<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/811.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">American Embassies at London, Paris,
                                        Berlin and St. Petersburg</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Identic telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-27">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>During the past week this Government has exchanged telegrams with
                                France, Germany, Great Britain, Japan and Russia, from which it
                                appears that while there is some divergence of opinion as to the
                                advisability of a small loan to the Peking Government at the present
                                juncture for administrative purposes, and as to what further
                                measures may be advisable in case the Shanghai conference fails of
                                satisfactory results, there is entire accord among the Governments
                                in the opinion that it is essential to maintain complete unity of
                                action by the powers.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>